# Portal UI Standards

When making changes under routes/components related to `/portal`, follow these rules to keep the UI consistent.

## Use shared components (preferred)
- Prefer `components/portal/*` when implementing any of the following:
  - Page headings/top action bars
  - Standard filter-sheet layout (Sheet with sticky footer buttons)
  - Shared portal loading/error/empty state patterns (especially for chart pages)

## Token discipline (required)
- Prefer theme tokens for color/typography:
  - `bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `bg-card`, `text-muted-foreground`, `border-input`
  - `text-primary-foreground`, `bg-primary`
  - `text-destructive-foreground`, `bg-destructive`
- Avoid hard-coded Tailwind gray/color classes in portal UI:
  - e.g. `text-gray-*`, `bg-gray-*`, `text-blue-*`, `bg-blue-*`, `text-red-*`, `bg-red-*`

## Typography scale (required)
- Use the portal heading components or follow a consistent hierarchy:
  - Page title: `text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight` (or `text-2xl` when space constrained)
  - Section titles: `text-lg md:text-xl font-semibold`
  - Supporting: `text-sm text-muted-foreground`
- Avoid ad-hoc mixes of `text-2xl` vs `text-3xl` for similar page titles.

## List/Table conventions
- Reuse `components/custom-table.tsx` for list/table wrappers.
- Empty state should match the shared `CustomTable` pattern: `No results.`

## Chart / analysis pages
- For chart-based report pages:
  - Show an error `Alert variant="destructive"` + a retry button
  - Show a skeleton while loading
  - Show a consistent empty state with a small outline button (Clear Filters / Retry)

## Forms & filter sheets
- Standard filter sheets should use the shared sheet width:
  - `w-full sm:w-[400px]`
- Field spacing:
  - `space-y-1.5` between `Label` and control
  - Use `grid` for multi-column field clusters
- Sticky bottom actions:
  - Primary: `Find ...`
  - Secondary: Clear with `FilterX`

